  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package is issued under the Minimal profile: a SHA-256 content hash is recorded but no digital signature is present, leaving structural integrity unverifiable (W-SI-01). All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels under the relaxed Minimal-profile threshold. Decision: Accepted.",
